:::summary
Real analysis is the rigorous mathematical study of the real number line and functions defined on it — the formal foundation that underlies calculus. Where calculus teaches you to compute derivatives and integrals, real analysis asks *why* those computations work, providing precise definitions, careful proofs, and the full theoretical apparatus behind limits, continuity, differentiation, and integration.
